&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adolfo Millabur &amp;Ntilde;ancuil: El trabajo del primer alcalde mapuche en Chile y su experiencia en el proceso constituyente Chileno.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*This event will be in Spanish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Una conversaci&amp;oacute;n con Adolfo Millabur &amp;Ntilde;ancuil, dirigente social y pol&amp;iacute;tico. En la Convenci&amp;oacute;n Constitucional representa al Pueblo Mapuche y electo v&amp;iacute;a Esca&amp;ntilde;os Reservados representantes de Pueblos Ind&amp;iacute;genas. Concejal de Tir&amp;uacute;a per&amp;iacute;odo 1992-1996, y alcalde de la misma comuna entre 1996 y 2021. Primer Alcalde Mapuche de la historia de Chile. Coordinador de la comisi&amp;oacute;n sobre Forma del Estado, Ordenamiento, Autonom&amp;iacute;a, Descentralizaci&amp;oacute;n, Equidad, Justicia Territorial, Gobiernos Locales y Organizaci&amp;oacute;n Fiscal. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SPEAKER: &lt;a href="https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__www.bcn.cl_historiapolitica_convencionales-5Fconstituyentes_ficha_Adolfo-5FMillabur-5F-25C3-2591ancuil&amp;amp;d=DwMFaQ&amp;amp;c=009klHSCxuh5AI1vNQzSO0KGjl4nbi2Q0M1QLJX9BeE&amp;amp;r=ot73TqWHE3Wyy3ZNUfz4uBM0hrWTHX4-X8HyMDk98i4&amp;amp;m=nAxYmMK_jAlvW2NEntjDr1GsWbXMOPCWArCba7sZmoCD6Fk6TZGBE8XfRALM6-cF&amp;amp;s=TTeoG6DoP_3hltZ0I3iJg-fYwuBpBaPIDwWusavdthw&amp;amp;e="&gt;Adolfo Millabur &amp;Ntilde;ancuil&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MODERATOR: &lt;a href="https://www.sipa.columbia.edu/faculty-research/faculty-directory/ben-orlove"&gt;Ben Orlove&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This program is provided by the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Irving Institute &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.irvinginstitute.columbia.edu/about-us/resources-and-cores/training-and-education-transform" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Training and Education&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.irvinginstitute.columbia.edu/about-us/resources-and-cores/training-and-education-transform" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;(TRANSFORM)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; Resource&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stats On Your Own - Four Sessions to Self-Reliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to be self-reliant in doing statistical analyses?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Stats on Your Own is a non-credit hybrid course: four 2-3-hour lecture videos and four in-person workshop sessions (with zoom option). This mini-course to Statistics Self-Reliance will help you to know how your data should be analyzed, or when you need to consult a biostatistician. Geared towards junior researchers (residents, fellows, and faculty), this workshop will help you become self-reliant in doing statistical analyses and to know:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. The correct statistical procedures to analyze one&amp;#39;s data&lt;br /&gt;
2. How to carry out the analyses&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;We will teach: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
1. The basic 2x2 contingency table using our online tool&lt;br /&gt;
2. The little that Excel can do (t-tests, correlations, scatter plots)&lt;br /&gt;
3. A simplified power analysis (sample size determination) using our online tool&lt;br /&gt;
4. More advanced analyses using the popular (free) software R, facilitated by our special-purpose R functions: anova (one-way, covariance, two-way, repeated measures), nonparametric analyses, linear regression, logistic regression, Kaplan-Meier, Cox&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The curriculum is comprehensive and will involve working with real data.&amp;nbsp;There will be four in-person (with zoom option) workshop sessions, with plenty of time to go over questions, clarifications, difficulties, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instructor:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
